SIMPLE: masterly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Masterly
<hw>Mas"ter*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Suitable to, or
characteristic of, a master; indicating thorough knowledge or superior
skill and power; showing a master's hand; <as>as, a <ex>masterly</ex>
design; a <ex>masterly</ex> performance; a <ex>masterly</ex>
policy.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧A wise and <xex>masterly</xex>
inactivity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir J. Mackintosh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Imperious; domineering; arbitrary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masterly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Masterly
<hw>Mas"ter*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With the skill of a
master.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou dost speak <qex>masterly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masterous</ent>⟦br⟧
